Sasalin shot out a jet of flame, setting a small patch of forest ablaze, then circled above, observing the timing. Strangely, when he slowed down, the eerie shrieks behind him also ceased. Sasalin forgot there was a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've turned into a Slak before!"
"Flying on your own and suddenly being dragged away by a huge pink dragon are two completely different things!"
"Still okay, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly disagreed with Nisi's statement; he looked paler than usual, and his claws had dug deeply into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slak, but Sasalin clearly didn't care. Nevertheless, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and landed in an open space.
"I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I smelled something. I need to take care of it!"
"You had to bring us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sasalin's back, sliding to the ground along the tail, and asked sharply. "We left Retwick behind! We abandoned that strong and aggressive big brute! How is he supposed to find us?"
“He’ll figure it out…”, Nisi nodded approvingly. “Retwick is slow to react, but not stupid.”
"Can Retwick drive a car?"
Nisi blinked her eyes and turned to look at Tenuk. "He can definitely drive a car."
"Have you ever seen Retwick drive a car? He doesn’t have a truck like you, and I’ve never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayel’s. He started taking the bus to work purely because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin suddenly burst into laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took Sasalin a while to calm down.
"I'm sorry, I'm sorry. I just imagined you, my big, armored friend, riding a little bicycle designed specifically for Temsens children. The image was too ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. The idea was so funny! I have to keep it well."
Kayel also laughed because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Well, well. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasalin grunted, took off, and disappeared quickly, then flew back and left a body in front of Nisi. It was an Orotharak, a very rare golden-white dragon creature. But its head was missing. "Another one is dead. I heard their cries. I smelled their blood. I must protect them and hunt the killer. This is the will of Ixini. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slak suddenly froze. Nisi and Kayel also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. A huge and dark creature was staring at them, hissing. The thing snapped its two pairs of massive wings open and charged forward, its target directly aimed at Sasalin, completely ignoring the three small figures between it and Sasalin. Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to dodge aside, but Nisi found herself pulled to the ground, almost flung onto Sasalin.
Sasalin grabbed Nisi with one hand, swung her onto his back with his long and agile tail, and took off into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly chased after them.
Kayel snorted, drew his rifle from behind, opened the bag, and took out a belt of bullets. He attached the bullet belt to his chest for easy access, but soon realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster were all gone.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you turn into a flying animal?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to chase after him?"
"Garbage talk."
"However... one of them is a giant monster!"
"That's nothing. My rifle here has strong firepower and can fire at any moment. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenuk hesitated for a moment, then took a step back to create some space for himself. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, and his arms transforming into wings. He quickly became an ordinary light-blue Slak, though his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Tenuk now looks like an ordinary Slak, with neatly arranged scales on his back and a pair of spines that make it easier for Kayel to grab. It took Tenuk a long time to get off the ground, but once he was airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and made a determined effort to catch up.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not facing only one opponent. A second dark monster burst out from beneath them, and Tenuk barely dodged the impact.
"I guess this must be the other terrifying big monster Larenex was worried about," Kayel frowned, trying to shoot at the second monster but missing, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond; he was too busy flying toward Nisi and Sasalin, despite the other monster chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to face the creature. Since the monster was chasing them, Kayel thought it was good news because it made aiming and shooting easier. Two bullets pierced through the monster's upper wing, and it howled in pain before disappearing into the forest. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it was definitely too slow to keep up.
Ahead, Sasalin was wildly flailing his body, spewing flames at the black monster, while Nisi desperately held on to Sasalin to prevent herself from falling. Although this monster was clearly injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs appeared to be doing little damage. After stabilizing himself, Nisi seized the opportunity to pull out her trusted shotgun. Of course, a shotgun wouldn't be effective against such a monster, but the scattered bullets at least might scare off this black beast?
